author: ezzy
title: "HF21" Hits the Airwaves
body:
*About time we had some positivity from the media hurled our way. It seems the buzz around the latest hardfork 21 isn't only confined to **Steemit**. Major crypto media websites are also getting the word out, with the likes of **Coindesk, PRNewswire and Cryptopolitan** getting involved. The hype train speeds up that little bit more.*
![HF21 testnet.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmeMBaVcrRag7qgSNXJHzDCABF72nb2Yh1iCd2Uvo8S1d8/HF21%20testnet.jpg)
Ever heard of that saying "All news is good news"? Well, I'll take this for what it is. The **STEEM** blockchain has been berated and chastized for far too long, which has proven to be one of a few huge drains on the overall growth of the platform. Investor confidence is at an all-time low as can be seen by the daily volume numbers. But that doesn't mean this will always be the case. Technically, we are head and sholuders above most of the top 100. We all know that but the external crypto masses don't. A significant change in sentiment is required and these latest developments are providing some much-meeded hope in that respect. The mantra of "70% lay offs" are fading fast. Thank the dear lord for that. But it's not over yet, by a long shot. If we've got the eyes on our current actions, we must ensure that the change over to this new economic model does what is says on the tin. Restores balance on **Steemit** and encourages "good" behaviour on the blockchain. The transition must be smooth and impressive to the watchful eye of the crypto media. If the ball has started rolling, momentum needs to be gathered. All steps thus far are potentially leading to a very favourable outcome, if things work out from here on. *I realize there are more than enough people here worried about the impending hardfork. I can't deny, I'm one of them. But if it's an inevitablity for the blockchain then I guess embracing it would be more productive for us in the longer term and thus learning to work with it rather than against it. I'll modify my actions on the blockchain in parrallel to the changes made. I hope we also do the same and allow the bigger voices outside to sing our praises for once instead of critizise and admonish. Fingers crossed things go according to plan. Only 11 days left now...*
![PAGE-DIVIDER.jpg](https://steemitimages.com/DQmSZ3NtRqFfQcDtxxQDM2jWnRNmcWECzd7AfAhMYgGiZTB/PAGE-DIVIDER.jpg)

Hope you enjoyed this post, please look out for more on the way... (author: @ezzy)

author: adsactly
title: ADSactly Poetry: Poetry: A Place of Many Answers
body:
https://i.imgur.com/0a2PeUx.jpg?1
[Source](https://impresa.prensa.com/vivir/poder-poesia_0_4127587279.html)
#
Poetry: A Place of Many Answers
#
https://i.imgur.com/368W8k2.png?1
# Hello, friends of @adsactly
These days it's rained in my city. I think I once told you how nice it is to read in the rain. With the rain it is as if the world stops and hearts open, so reading a good book can be a pleasant and unique experience. # With the rain, poetry floats in the air, so I prefer to take poetic anthologies that allow me to be in tune with the environment and with the feelings that the rain awakens when it falls. I've had this fascination with poetry since I was a child. I still remember the days when, in cultural events held at the school, I recited the poems of **Andrés Eloy Blanco, Antonio Machado, Pablo Neruda and Gabriela Mistral**, but also many romantic poems by late-night and unknown poets. #
https://i.imgur.com/79YH2Lm.jpg?1
[Source](http://www.surysur.net/eduardo-persico-a-veces-la-poesia/)
Then came adolescence, a passionate taste for reading, a familiarity with the written word, a strong need for expression and a bubbling load of emotions. I knew that poetry is not only about crying, it is also about falling in love and that as a weapon of expression it is sublime and deadly. Right now I think it is curious how sensitivity is formed in people. # As **Gabriel García Márquez** says, many times we get to good literature through mediocre authors and I think that's what happened to me. In my youth I read many anodyne and insignificant writers, but as I grew up and got to know, books by great poets came into my hands that made me see the world not only how others saw it, but how I saw it from within. One of those writers who influenced not only to see me but to question me as a woman and a person, was **Antonia Palacios**. #
https://i.imgur.com/hqEte75.jpg?1
[Antonia Palacios](https://anamariavelazquezanderson.blogspot.com/2016/05/antonia-palacios-y-la-perfeccion-de-la.html)
**Antonia Palacios** was a Venezuelan writer and one of the most outstanding female voices in poetry of the last century. With a solid intellectual formation, she was the first woman to win, in 1976, the National Literature Prize. With her famous novel Ana Isabel, a decent girl, she made her way into the literary circles of the country, and then became a great poet with her collections of poems: **Textos del desalojo (Eviction Texts - 1973), Ese oscuro animal del sueño (That dark animal of the dream -1991), Hondo temblor de lo secreto (Deep tremor of the secret -1993)**, among others. # Most of his poetry is autobiographical, intimate, confessional. Written is prose, develops the theme of the house, solitude, nightlife, memory and the body. In his collection of poems Textos del desalojo, there is a beautiful poem that says: >I am here in the dark with my back to the light, forgetting the beginning, the eternity of the day. I am here ignored, the profile of my face lost in the shadow. I am here diminished, barely a line, a point without relief. I am here inclined, letting the night pass over me. Outside in space The immense eagles battle with the wind. I am here waiting... And I pick up my gestures, and I withdraw my breath, I gag my voice and all I am silence hidden in the dark. I am here vigilant, watching in fear a wandering creature that has stopped in me. # In this poem we see how the lyrical voice speaks to us from the darkness, with the sensation of insignificance, from within, as if waiting for the right moment to leave, to show itself. With these lines we perceive the moment of withdrawal that any human being can have in life, not to stalk, but to heal, to know oneself. The being isolates himself, he goes into the darkness to find clarity in himself and in others. Like cracked objects that can only show their fissures when they have light inside. #
https://i.imgur.com/FooaINE.jpg?1
[Source](https://es.dreamstime.com/foto-de-archivo-mujer-perdida-en-oscuridad-image47112130)
In **Hondo temblor de lo secreto** we will find poems that also talk about space, the body and light. Like the one I share with you below: >Going overflowing without knowing it. Going off in a shaking light. Going off almost diminished in a thinness of wounding edge. To be lost in the absences, without the skin, without the rubbing, without breath. Leaving without form, without presence. Go slowly turning into dust, dust blown by the wind. # This beautiful poem confronts us with a sense of emptiness and darkness, of how we can feel that we are dissipating, disappearing each day with each experience. It is not a complete disintegration, but a reaction as a consequence of living. Let us observe that dust is the matter into which we become: a dust from which we have come out and to which we will inevitably return. #
https://i.imgur.com/22SMBTM.jpg?1
[Source](https://pxhere.com/es/photo/1280458)
In the same previous book of poems, we will find poems that no longer speak of spaces, but of the body and life, like the one I transcribe below: >There are still lips, eyes that look at things. Arms are raised in an attempt to fly. The sex is still throbbing, still wet. And this falling of the dew in the secret thickness of my already naked forest. # Time can be a predator, an enemy, of objects, spaces and people. Human beings may not know it, but time does not ask, but it always answers. Sometimes, it is necessary to remind others and to remind ourselves that we still exist, that in spite of time and adversity, something remains of us. In this poem, the lyrical voice rescues important feminine parts that still remain intact, ready, if you like, to wait for a discovery. #
https://i.imgur.com/KgeoBn4.jpg?1
[Source](https://pxhere.com/es/photo/1446009)
I have to admit that I miss the vertiginous and exciting sensation of reading an excellent collection of poems and being lost, feverish, but happy for the reading. Because for me poetry will always be a solitary, sincere, abyssal search; a look inwards to discover questions, answers, a certain light. Finally, I believe that poetry, like any exercise in spirituality, allows us to reach a certain plenitude or consciousness. Like the poems of **Antonia Palacios**: poetry departs from darkness to reach light. Our light. # ___ # I hope you enjoyed reading this post. I remind you that you can vote for @adsactly as a witness and join our server in discord. Until a next smile. ;)
#
https://i.imgur.com/368W8k2.png?1
# ###
BIBLIOGRAPHICAL REFERENCE
https://poetasvenezolanas.com/2017/07/22/ocho-poemas-de-antonia-palacios-caracas-venezuela-1904-2001/ https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonia_Palacios # Written by: @nancybriti --- --- #
Click the coin below to join our Discord Server
[![Adsactly Logo Newest 300dpi.png]((https://i.imgur.com/2REClJX.png))](https://discord.gg/pcDQShW)
--- #
We would greatly appreciate your [witness vote](https://steemit.com/~witnesses)
To vote for @adsactly-witness please click the link above, then find "adsactly-witness" and click the upvote arrow or scroll to the bottom and type "adsactly-witness" in the box
#
Thank You
---

author: lionsuit
title: Inception (2010) - The Shooting Script
body:
![IMG_20190729_014036427.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmPey4z88vpfSaVEHuJaYTj5tTNKLCAjy18cciDmxazANT/IMG_20190729_014036427.jpg)

I am more excited about getting a copy  of this script than I would have expected.

15 times. If I had to guess, I've seen Inception 15 times. I watched it again last week. The deeper  you  look, the deeper you see. Nolan is a master on so many fronts. You want action, adventure, sci-fi, romance, drama, humor? It's all here.

You want a master class on motif, color, lighting, editing? It's all here.

This last viewing had me looking at editing and composition more than most other things.

Here we have two characters discuss what will become the most dangerous part of the story, a dance with limbo, not waking up. We don't say it here in the description of the scene, but we do lean in, both characters, one after another, the  characters themselves creating a tighter shot, a  more dramatic composition. The captain and the chemist.

![IMG_20190729_014215106.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmUVvRdJ4mAu6NbV5CXfGZYo48B462Kwxp6TdC6kbtLMQC/IMG_20190729_014215106.jpg)

Just one interesting note from my first look over. It's underscored with italics.
"A *powerful* sedative."

---

Be well.
[LionSuit.com](http://www.lionsuit.com)
(images and words are original.)

author: parkname
title: 산초와 방아향이 가득한 수제비, 울산 "저수지휴게실"
body:
![title_image](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/565/post/41709/content_4472060b-735b-47f8-9a5e-39e0bf7de4bf.jpeg)
현지인이 수제비가 맛있다고 소개한 식당. 그곳에서 산초와 방아향 때문에 이문화 체험 제대로 한 식당을 소개할게요. 이 식당은 울산 울주군 청량읍에 있는 "저수지휴게실"입니다. 이 식당 앞에 [아래사진]과 같은 두현 저수지가 있습니다. [두현저수지] ![20190827_140844.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207343/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [식당전경] ![20190827_135317.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207334/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [메뉴] 저는 매운수제비(산초, 방아), 일반수제비, 만두를 주문했습니다. 여기서 매운수제비에 있는 산초와 방아는 선택이 아닌 필수입니다. ![20190827_135409.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207333/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [매운수제비] 매운수제비를 먹으려고 주문했으나 산초와 방아향이 나에겐 맞지 않아 일반 수제비로 방향 전환했습니다. 하지만 테이블의 80%는 이 매운 수제비가 자리를 차지했답니다. ![20190827_142711.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207335/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [일반수제비] 양이 좀 적어 보이는 것이 약간 흠이긴 하나 찐한 국물과 쫄깃한 수제비는 일품이었습니다. ![20190827_142528.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207336/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [만두] 제가 일명 "귀요미 만두"로 불렀습니다. 왕만두 등을 생각하다가 이렇게 작은 만두를 보니 새샘 신기했답니다. ![20190827_140444.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207337/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) [만두속] 만두속은 이렇게 여리게 생겼답니다. ![20190827_140547.jpg](https://static.tasteem.io/uploads/image/image/207344/4904178c-4b12-4c46-856f-b6220805ff42.jpeg) 산초와 방아가 들어간 수제비..이문화체험 제대로 했네요. --------------------- #### 맛집정보 ### 저수지휴게실 ![score](https://static.tasteem.io/images/steem/1Crowns.png) [대한민국 울산광역시 울주군 청량면 문죽리 1213](https://kr.tasteem.io/post/41709#map) -----------------------------------------
[산초와 방아향이 가득한 수제비, 울산 "저수지휴게실"](https://kr.tasteem.io/post/41709)
이 글은 Tasteem 컨테스트 [내가 소개하는 이번 주 맛집](https://kr.tasteem.io/event/558)에 참가한 글입니다.
[테이스팀은 무엇인가요?](https://kr.tasteem.io/about) [![tasteem_banner.png](https://static.tasteem.io/images/tasteem_banner_v3.png)](https://kr.tasteem.io)

author: christopherb
title: ¡EL MEJOR JUEGO DE AGILIDAD MENTAL! | Puzzles Inteligentes - Gameplay #01
body:
# <center> Sup steemians!! </center>

<center> **Desde que tengo memoria** siempre me he sentido atraído por los rompecabezas y juegos que requieren rapidez mental. Se me hacen super divertidos e interesantes, ya que debes estar sumamente concentrado y pendiente de todo lo que sucede en el momento. Por ello, hace unos días me di a la tarea de buscar **una aplicación de móvil** que tuviera el estilo rompecabezas que tanto amaba de niño, y así fue como encontré: _**"Puzzles Inteligentes"**_ de **Pixign.** Un juego que la verdad, me está encantando. Desde el día que descargué el juego. hasta la fecha, no he podido dejar de jugar, por lo que no tuve necesidad de pensarlo más de dos veces para compartírselos. </center>

![portada.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmTS4gWVyPGSpc621QhEST3KkHAUMAQTdTouMRknvzoo98/portada.png)

![coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmapWu1zQmfPiPt75bjVvnEYR5f4k45JcNQuESfy16qPz4/coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png)

<center> **Di inicio a mi investigación** preguntándome cual seria la mejor manera de presentarlo. Se me ocurrieron dos formas; _con un post dedicado a él o en un video gameplay._ Tras darle varias vueltas en mi cabeza **decidí unir ambos conceptos,** y así poder mostrarles el juego que tan entregado me ha tenido estos últimos días. </center> 

<center> **Pero antes, quiero que lo conozcan un poco más.** </center> 

<center> _**"Puzzles Inteligentes"**_ es un juego de agilidad mental, desarrollada por la empresa **Pixign.** </center>

<center> ![Imagen1.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmVXi7DoeWA5cqg43cFRoZD3YWJLQKSDfnC5jJpsKPjuWH/Imagen1.png) </center> 

<center> Posee diferentes ejercicios mentales usando **laberintos, bloques, números  y  coincidencias,** los cuales se dividen cada uno por grado de dificultad. Comenzamos solucionando los ejercicios en _**Simple,**_ luego avanzamos a _**Normal,**_ desbloqueamos así el _**Extra,**_ y nos abrimos paso por _**Difícil, Muy Difícil, Imposible**_ hasta llegar a _**Rey.**_ Este nivel posee un grado de dificultad muy avanzado. </center>

![Screenshot_20190810-0126082.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmcJsU6cDSczZykvJc3S2jdQAJVMkegKwfezkhT3MZqzNJ/Screenshot_20190810-0126082.png)

<center> **En el siguiente video** verán un poco de la jugabilidad que tiene _**"Puzzles Inteligentes"**_ y lo mucho que sufro y tardo para pasarlo, tan solo en el **nivel Simple.** </center>

<center> **¡Espero les guste!** </center>

<center> _**El siguiente video usa el juego desarrollado por Pixign "Puzzles Inteligentes", ambientado con una banda sonora original de e-soundtrax.**_ </center>

![coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmapWu1zQmfPiPt75bjVvnEYR5f4k45JcNQuESfy16qPz4/coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png)

# <center> ¡EL MEJOR JUEGO DE AGILIDAD MENTAL! | Puzzles Inteligentes - Gameplay #01 </center>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gEKAl_OMrtg

![coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmapWu1zQmfPiPt75bjVvnEYR5f4k45JcNQuESfy16qPz4/coleccion-ornamentos-texto-dibujados-mano_23-214767117122.png)

<center> **¡Muchas gracias por haber llegado hasta acá! Si les gustó este primer post y video, estilo gameplay, de apreciación a "Puzzles Inteligentes" de Pixign no duden en hacermelo saber en los comentarios. ¡Pronto vendrán más, un gran abrazo!** </center>

![ChristopherB - Animado.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmdEMwAzvC7Av1S8hHz5WkcoFapoksQKp1tNzJdBLgiCjm/ChristopherB%20-%20Animado.png)

How to plant trees with @treeplanter

  1. Transfer between 0.01 and 0.2 STEEM/SBD to my wallet, with the link in memo of the post or comment you want to have upvoted by me.
  2. I will upvote the post and attempt to add 100% value per vote per STEEM/SBD you send, so 0.01 STEEM/SBD donation = approx 0.02 STEEM/SBD worth of vote, up to 0.2 STEEM/SBD = 0.4 STEEM/SBD worth of vote - in case of non-self votes. If you want to be self-voted you will get 20% more of your donation, so 0.01 STEEM/SBD donation = approx 0.012 STEEM/SBD worth of vote, up to 0.2 STEEM/SBD = 0.24 STEEM/SBD worth of vote.

What happens to your donations/upvote?

  1. At least 50% of it is going directly to Cameroon to fund our conservation program to save Abongphen Highland Forest
  2. 50% will help me to get more STEEM POWER to plant more trees in the future as well as to run the bot properly

EACH DOLLAR (sent to Cameroon)
=
1 TREE PLANTED

PLANT A TREE AND GET PAID FOR IT.
IT WOULD BE NICE IF SEND IT AS FREE UP VOTE GIFT TO SOMEBODY!

Rules of @treeplanter

  1. Each post/comment could be upvoted by me only once – if you send the same post/comment again, your contribution is going to be considered as donation without upvoting
  2. If you transfer less than 0.01 STEEM/SBD, It is going to be considered as donation without upvoting.
  3. If you transfer more than 0.2 STEEM/SBD, I will upvote the post as the donation is 0.2 STEEM/SBD, the rest is just a donation – thank you for it.
  4. The maximum daily upvotes are equal to 10 - fully 100% upvotes - keeping voting power as close to 98% as much as possible
  5. If the Voting Power of @treeplanter gets exhausted you will be queued – your link will get @treeplanter’s upvote immediately when the VP is recharged back. If the link will get expired before @treeplanter is able to upvote it you will get refunded.
  6. Post to be upvoted have to be maximun 4 days old when the bot will upvote it or it donation will be refunded.

author: tmroot
title: How to choose a carpet cleaning professional
body:
Choosing a carpet cleaning professional can be a daunting task. There is much to know and much to be careful. The tips below can help you make the right decision. For the best service, we recommend this [rug cleaning](https://www.singaporecarpetcleaning.com/).

![](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmRGDFdKXPHKh31rXgBsRyDiHoVTdKNVTGzxcoQjXum1Ho/image.png)

**Tip # 1 Choose your carpet cleaner with a good reputation.** That sounds obvious, but many people simply choose a name from a phone book and then expect the best. It is better to try to verify them first. Many carpet cleaners can have testimonials on their site. And, of course, that is a good sign. But even if they have testimonials, you'll know that they would never post comments from customers who had a bad experience with them. And then, in that case, you may want to go to an independent third-party review site, such as Yelp. Or search online for local reviews. 

**Tip # 2 Make sure the company has competent workers.** They may have the newest and the best equipment, but without good workers, you will not get the most out of your money. Or, as with other companies, they can attract you with a low price, but suddenly you discover that there are additional charges that appear on your bill from all directions. If your price is low, it may be a good deal. But don't let that low price blind you to the potential dangers behind it.
 
**Tip # 3 Be careful when choosing a cleaner based on price alone.** Carpet cleaning is like anything else. You often get what you pay for. Now that said, it must also be realistic. If the carpet is old or in poor condition, there may be little that a cleaner can do to restore it to something that resembles again. 

**Tip # 4 Look for a guarantee.** If a cleaner is worth its salt, there must provide a guarantee. Although guarantees are often money back, some may offer a satisfaction guarantee, which means they will continue working on their carpets until they are satisfied with the result. While it may seem impossible to judge the quality of your workers in advance, there is something you can look for and that will help you in this department. It is called cleaning and restoration certification (IICRC). If they have one, they probably include it on their website. However, some do not include it on your site. If they don't have one, you can ask them if they have one. They may not have thought about putting it in place because it is not something that many people know. 

**Tip # 5 Try to organize a free inspection.** Many carpet cleaners will give you a free inspection and budget in the hope of getting the job. When you think you have found a good one, accept it with this offer. You can then read your cleaner better after talking with him/her face to face. If you don't see a free inspection/estimate on your website, ask about one. It is a standard practice in the industry and will not seem like a misplaced request. When you think you have found a good one, accept it with this offer. You can then read your cleaner better after talking with him/her face to face. 

If you don't see a free inspection/estimate on your website, ask about one. It is a standard practice in the industry and will not seem like a misplaced request. When you think you have found a good one, accept it with this offer. You can then read your cleaner better after talking with him/her face to face. If you don't see a free inspection/estimate on your website, ask about one. It is a standard practice in the industry and will not seem like a misplaced request.

body:
I AM

I'm living a life I'm still despising
On this level there is no realizing
It's gone beyond purgatory
I am stuck in hell

I am in this place where those who died here dwell

I'm not a ghost hunter they simply hunt me
Still I've never seen one
But I can sense them
Everywhere I work
Everywhere I go 
You think it's a joke
But I won't provoke

The spirits I know are already here
There is no true standard by which to adhere
To provoke hatred
Instead of embracing the sacred
This place is jaded

Welcome to hell
Is what I was told
It's obvious
Our lives have been sold
So far down the river
I drink and kill my liver

I can't complain

All of those who were slain
With nothing to gain

I don't understand why you target me
Why I'm the targeted individual
It's clear to me you cannot see
When you die your hate shall be residual

Unjust
Nepotists
The fucking point
You're sure to miss
A life gone amiss
Scars my mindset
I've used restraint
I've tried hard not to mind it

Just as a suicide bomber
You have provided no training
It's clear you have no honor

A death occurs
A mind disturbed
A soul is lost 
Just at what cost?

author: portalmine
title: Ich habe eine "Idee", will jemand mitmachen?
body:
### Jetzt wirds [DEEP](/@deepnet)<sub><sub>(Vielleicht)</sub></sub>
Ich bin zwar so überhaupt gar nicht für STEEM geeignet, da ich selten Themen habe und diese noch seltener interessant formulieren könnte, allerdings bin ich trotzdem nie vom Netz gegangen, weil ich hier einfach ein bisschen mit APIs (für die man sich nicht anmelden muss) rumprobieren konnte und damit auch etwas besser mit Python umgehen gelernt habe.
Bis ich im Oktober mit meinem Informatikstudium anfange habe ich dazwischen im Groben nur noch eine Woche Urlaub und würde in dieser Zeit gern nochmal ein "Projekt" starten. Während ich aber bis jetzt immer allein gemacht habe, was nicht allzu effektiv war, wollte ich diesmal vorher fragen, ob noch jemand mitbauen wollen würde.
Vor ein paar Tagen habe ich den Account @deepnet erstellt, auf dem das Projekt, falls es eines wird, vorgestellt und dokumentiert werden sollte.
#### Wozu denn noch eine Sidechain?
STEEM ist das Soziale Netzwerk, die SteemEngine hat viele neue Währungen und Möglichkeiten auf die STEEM-Blockchain gebracht. Dennoch würde ich den Ansatz des Sozialen Netzwerkes mit eigenen Gruppen und eigenen Währungen noch einmal angehen wollen. Denn im Grunde ist STEEM zwar Social Media, aber SteemEngine ist in erster Linie noch eine Exchange ohne direkte Möglichkeit eigene Smart Contracts zu veröffentlichen und STEEM ist auch nicht perfekt und ist es möglicherweise nach dem nächsten Update noch weniger.
Ein komplettes Netzwerk im Schatten, soll heißen in ["custom_json"](https://developers.steem.io/apidefinitions/broadcast-ops#broadcast_ops_custom_json), ["custom_binary"](https://developers.steem.io/apidefinitions/broadcast-ops#broadcast_ops_custom_binary) und/oder ["custom"](https://developers.steem.io/apidefinitions/broadcast-ops#broadcast_ops_custom) Operationen, würde vielleicht für einige Fälle Vorteile bringen. Zum Beispiel könnten sich vielleicht viel schneller neue Plattformen/Gruppen bilden und entwickeln. Mit "entwickeln" ist in dem Fall das Experimentieren mit Auszahlungen usw. gemeint.
Bei SteemEngine gibt es ja teilweise das "Problem", dass man nicht nur mit z.B. PAL voten kann, ohne auch einen Vote mit STEEM und allen anderen vorhandenen Tokens zu verteilen. Wofür man auf STEEM mehrere Accounts braucht, könnte man im Schattennetzwerk, mit weit weniger Aufwand erledigen.

Also, wenn ihr Kritik üben wollt, kommentiert auf STEEM.
Und wenn ihr interessiert seid, dann könnt ihr vielleicht einen gewissen ziemlich ruhigen [Discord](https://discord.gg/HCxBwc) beleben. Auf STEEM gibt es schon zwei Posts unter `#deepnet`, deshalb nehmen wir eben #deepnetwork als Alternative.
***
<center>__Dank fürs Lesen und Kommentieren!__</center>

author: gduran
title: Steem is Still going for the New ATL
body:
![image.png](https://ipfs.busy.org/ipfs/QmYNvMwaWysLxXNadNXstesq86SqQcb1a1YKRRoWnnsGp5)
![image.png](https://ipfs.busy.org/ipfs/QmboydpaDbJcF8xgy4JBPnMkvGDr18EweCW1UxWtMGgzyU)

Well Steem is at $0.1875 right now and Bitcoin is very close to twelve thousand, to me it seems that when Bitcoin goes up Steem goes down, perhaps we have to wait for Bitcoin to crash to see some action in Steem?

Of course now I see people all over saying that it will go all the way down to ten cents and even all the way to one cent, and the hypothetical down to zero value and someone asked if we would still use Steem at a price of zero. Now let's be serious there, the only stimulation we have for writing on Steemit is getting some money because there is no other, hardly anyone reads what you write and with zero value that is exactly what you would get zero readers so why waste your time?

Now why does Steem behave in this manner? Could it be that Stinc wants it to go down as far as it can so we can stock up on it and strike it rich when it shoots sky high? I doubt that, Steem is just not marketable at this moment very few people are willing to invest in it, perhaps they are waiting for Voice (EOS) or LIBRA (Facebook) to come out and see how they behave? No I don't think so either, Steem is just a little fish in a huge ocean, people (investors) lost interest in it a long time ago.

Is this giving up on Steemit? No I will be here as long as the coin has at least some value, at zero I am gone. But there are some things here that really strike me as odd, for example not too long ago we had a post by STinc's, well I really can't remember her position in the company, but she clearly stated that ad income was so good STinc would soon stop selling Steem on the market. Yet I read a lot of posts saying that they still sell Steem and not only that, the amount has not diminished. So what happened with the ad income?

As you can see from the two images above (taken from https://coinmarketcap.com/) it seems that Steem and Bitcoin are mirror images, while BTC has been going up, Steem has been going down, there is some mystical thing going on there, when we manage to decipher what it is, we will finally be able to go sky high.

So, are we going to go down to $0.01, who knows everything is possible, I was really thinking it would go down to $0.15, but with all this gloom I have revised it to $0.10, maybe lower, but I really, really hope at some point it hits bottom and even if very slowly it starts going up, the platform can't afford Steem to be so low and we can't either, it is devastating, while I have a lot of patience it is because I am stubborn I know most others are more realistic and will quit long before I do.
root_title: Steem is Still going for the New ATL

author: boddhisattva
title: MONOMAD PHOTOGRAPHIC CHALLENGE - Sunny day at nature
body:
Special for @brumest's monomad photographic challenge.

I took this photo a couple of years ago during a family walk in nature.

As usual, trying to make a black and white version of this photo, I decided to experiment a little. I usually prefer high contrast black and white photos, often close to low key. As an experiment, I decided to make the picture closer to the high key. Such a black and white photo looks completely different. But, in my opinion, it is also very interesting.

What do you think?

Nikon D5000 + Sigma AF 17-50

I strongly recommend to open the photo in a separate tab to appreciate it.

Do you like this post? You can see more of my works in my blog @boddhisattva
root_title: MONOMAD PHOTOGRAPHIC CHALLENGE - Sunny day at nature

author: varwek
title: Learning Ansible 2.7 3rd Edition
body:
![Learning Ansible 2.7 3rd Edition.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmVU86S9DoGHPrp8jDw4asuS8qZRsU7ZUgLqc46ue6Mpbw/Learning%20Ansible%202.7%203rd%20Edition.png)

Use Ansible to configure your systems, deploy software, and orchestrate advanced IT tasks

Key Features

Get familiar with the fundamentals of Ansible 2.7
Understand how to use Ansible Tower to scale your IT automation
Gain insights into how to develop and test Ansible playbooks
Book Description

Ansible is an open source automation platform that assists organizations with tasks such as application deployment, orchestration, and task automation. With the release of Ansible 2.7, even complex tasks can be handled much more easily than before.

Learning Ansible 2.7 will help you take your first steps toward understanding the fundamentals and practical aspects of Ansible by introducing you to topics such as playbooks, modules, and the installation of Linux, Berkeley Software Distribution (BSD), and Windows support. In addition to this, you will focus on various testing strategies, deployment, and orchestration to build on your knowledge.

The book will then help you get accustomed to features including cleaner architecture, task blocks, and playbook parsing, which can help you to streamline automation processes. Next, you will learn how to integrate Ansible with cloud platforms such as Amazon Web Services (AWS) before gaining insights into the enterprise versions of Ansible, Ansible Tower and Ansible Galaxy. This will help you to use Ansible to interact with different operating systems and improve your working efficiency.

By the end of this book, you will be equipped with the Ansible skills you need to automate complex tasks for your organization.

What you will learn

Create a web server using Ansible
Write a custom module and test it
Deploy playbooks in the production environment
Troubleshoot networks using Ansible
Use Ansible Galaxy and Ansible Tower during deployment
Deploy an application with Ansible on AWS, Azure and DigitalOcean

Who this book is for

This beginner-level book is for system administrators who want to automate their organization's infrastructure using Ansible 2.7. No prior knowledge of Ansible is required

https://www.softwe.top/2019/08/learning-ansible-27-3rd-edition.html

author: robertbcoach
title: Origin of Life: Intelligence Required
body:
Esta es la Verdad, detrás del origen de la vida, Origen de la Vida - Inteligencia Requerida: ¿Puede la vida generarse espontáneamente a partir de productos químicos? ¿O se requieren instrucciones detalladas? En este video de Science Uprising se investiga el origen de la vida y cómo científicos materialistas (ateístas) como Stephen Hawking, afirmaron que la vida quirúrgica espontáneamente de los productos químicos sin ninguna guía o diseño inteligente. Los expertos que aparecen en este episodio incluyen James Tour, TT y WF Chao Profesor de Química, Profesor de Ciencias de la Computación y Profesor de Ciencias Materiales y Nanoingeniería, en la Universidad de Rice. Douglas Axe, profesor visitante de biología molecular Maxwell, Universidad de Biola y autor: "cómo confirma la biología nuestra intuición de que la vida está destinada;" y Stephen Meyer, PhD, Director, Centro de Ciencia y Cultura, Discovery Institute y autor de: El ADN y la evidencia para el diseño inteligente. title: Victoria Falls
body:
Victoria Falls is the largest waterfall in the world. It is about 1.7km wide and 108m high. It is located between the two countries Zambia and Zambabwe. Victoria Falls was discovered in 1855 by the Scottish explorer Dr. David Livingstone. It is one of the Seven Natural Wonders of the World. ---------- Video provided by Nocopyright ---------- Track: Culture Code - Feel Again (feat. author: wisdomandjustice
title: (Korean War History)Post #56. The Division of Korea, 1945-1948.
body:
Prof. Kathryn Weathersby

Given the importance of the Korean issue to the Soviet Union, the Soviet leadership closely monitored the actions taken toward holding elections in the South. On April 24 the Politburo, the highest decision-making body, sent instructions to General Shtykov in Pyongyang regarding the response the authorities in the North should make if separate elections are held in the South. In such case, Kim Il Sung should convene a special session of the People’s Assembly of North Korea to adopt two decisions worked out by the Politburo. 

First, Pyongyang had to counter the claims that a government in Seoul would have legal jurisdiction over the North. Therefore, the Assembly must declare that until Korea is unified, the draft constitution for the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea that the People’s Assembly had adopted that month should be considered the legal authority on the territory of North Korea. 

Second, the North must create a Korea-wide government to rival that created in Seoul. To claim legitimacy, this government would be created through elections held in both halves of the peninsula. Therefore, “two-stage illegal elections” would be held in the South. Each region would elect seven or eight representatives to meet in Haeju. They would then elect 360 deputies to the Supreme People’s Assembly from the southern provinces. According to Russian reports, around 1,100 South Korean representatives met in Haeju from August 21 to 26 and duly elected the 360 deputies. At the same time, elections were held in the North on August 25. 

    Just over two weeks after the establishment of the Republic of Korea, the Supreme People’s Assembly convened in Pyongyang with 572 deputies. On September 8 the Assembly approved the new Constitution and the following day the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea was established. General N. G. Lebedev recalled in an interview with historian Andrei Lankov that it was he who suggested the name for the new state, after rejecting the name “Korean People’s Republic” that had been proposed by the North Koreans. Kim Il Sung became head of the Cabinet of Ministers while Kim Tu-bong remained chairman of the Supreme People’s Assembly.

Since the Republic of Korea claimed legitimacy because of recognition by the United Nations, the DPRK based its legitimacy on an assertion that it was the only government created independently by Koreans. Ignoring the central role played by the Soviet Union, this new narrative located the origin of the state in the North-South Conference that had been held in Pyongyang in April 1948, just before the UN Temporary Commission on Korea carried out its plan to conduct elections.

Kim Ku and Kim Kyu-sik had attended the week-long North-South Conference and had returned with a promise from Kim Il Sung that he would accept free elections in the north and would refrain from cutting off the supply of electricity to the South. Both promises were soon broken, but, believing them to be true, Kim Kyu-sik had boycotted the UN sponsored elections. The newly created DPRK therefore asserted that it had been established through the North-South Conference by anti-Japanese fighters led by Kim Il Sung, while the ROK was an American creation led by Japanese collaborators.

In the next post, we will examine the approaches the ROK and DPRK initially took toward the tragic division of Korea into two competing states.  

[Sources: This post relies on Andrei Lankov, From Stalin to Kim Il Sung: The Formation of North Korea, 1945-1960 (New Brunswick, NJ: Rutgers University Press, 2002).]


Posted from my blog with SteemPress : http://warandpeace.dothome.co.kr/2019/08/01/korean-war-historypost-56-the-division-of-korea-1945-1948/

![FlexibilityExercise.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmWXPrkXqomdE14dXEeizWb7xxyh7tfJPriTc4WBhxNaxP/FlexibilityExercise.jpg)

Flexibility and mobility are two different concepts, although they are often confused as being the same.

Flexibility is the capacity of a material to deform without breaking and regain his initial form after the force that cause it to deform stops to apply any pressure on it.

Mobility is the capacity of a mechanical part to move unobstructed by anything.

Often when people lose their mobility in their joints, they try increasing the flexibility of that joint in the hope that it will become more mobile.

This concepts are not synonymous, you can have a flexible and immobile joint. You could be as flexible as a contortionist and still have a low amount of mobility in your joints.

The loss of mobility happens do to the misalignment of the joints, for example if your pelvis is tilted to 30 degrees forward when it is in a neutral position, your capacity to bend forward from the hips is going to be decreased by 30 degrees.

If you stretch the hips you are going to increase the amount of flexibility you have in the hips but not the mobility of the hips.

Your hips are going to be able to deform without breaking any tissue and be restored to their original shape but they are not moving unobstructed by anything, because your pelvis is still tilted at 30 degrees.

In order to actually increase mobility in that joint you would have to realign the pelvis so it is in a neutral position when your hip joints are completely open.

And your pelvis is probably misaligned do to the joint equilibrium overcompensation principle.

So working with the muscles around the hips and legs won't change the alignment of the pelvis and hip joints, just increase the capacity of those muscles to deform without breaking.

Mobility is more important than flexibility, you could argue that being flexible is more of a party trick than everything else. If you are very flexible you can do some yoga poses take pictures of it and upload it to your social media page to get a lot of likes.

Mobility on the other hand it is a matter of health, if you want to be able to tie your own shoe laces when you get old, do all the activities that you enjoy and be free of pain, you need to remain mobile.

You need to have a propper body alignment inorder for your joints to be able to move unobstructed by anything.

body:
![Screenshot_20190820-122324_Brave.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmdaXvtn22NuGtFuMCsRVPTpF45ut1BQSw7fQSuPTjo5cS/Screenshot_20190820-122324_Brave.jpg)
[Image Source](https://www.intrepreneur.life/int/@crystalhuman/learn-and-earn-complete-quests-and-get-tokens-it-s-easy)

We live in amazing times now. At one point in time starting a business was extremely difficult. It required immense capital, and connections to even think of starting a business. Of course, it's no cakewalk now but thanks to technology, information collection, idea vetting and access to capital are no longer difficult. 

Let me explain. The internet has created many success stories and those that started businesses early on now sit at the top any rich list you look at. In fact their wealth overshadows that of old school businessmen. So how does one become a successful entrepreneur. The below picture explains a lot, but I will share my thoughts below -
![Screenshot_20190820-152920_Chrome.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmUC7ppWMLtU4jxrq3N9u8cRWi6WP65rqYdyzZWCuzE3uy/Screenshot_20190820-152920_Chrome.jpg)
[Image Source](http://www.apn.report/2017/12/29/developing-entrepreneurship-skills-in-a-secondary-science-classroom/)

Quick to identify opportunities and ideas 

![images.png](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmNhsU51LhaoVTaG5YpcVSPnJxbkM9mguMuy8kw6NeTSmP/images.png)
[Image source](https://medium.com/@dariusforoux/15-life-changing-ideas-ceeece7f4ca0)

The internet has made it possible to find an audience for anything. There's people consuming content about other people consuming content or watching people be a glutton on YouTube. In fact in business school, we were once asked to find ways to add value to a pen. We had 50 plus ideas for a new pen. Very often people think, all ideas have been exhausted, no that's not the case. Successful entrepreneurs spot ideas better and early on.

Have Discipline and Perseverance 

![faith.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmYtfzZZdqy1Q9cw153u6sWuwZepWUsUssFbadqai4dd9R/faith.jpg)
[Image source](http://www.allaboutseniors.org/perseverance-the-muscle-that-needs-a-daily-workout)

Having self belief and belief in the idea is super important for an entrepreneur. Only then can you sell your idea. Also the journey to success isn't easy. Most stories about successful entrepreneurs will tell you that they were under tremendous financial stress at one point and that they lived in conditions, none of us would ever want to be in. Successful entrepreneurs also face failures but they get up after every fall and keep inching forward.

Ability to Understand People

![SOCIAL-LYING-HOW-WAS-YOUR-DAY.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmQHAfwKSsTsRY1uNEgTVfaJVsas9ohF4YZynoxanzXubQ/SOCIAL-LYING-HOW-WAS-YOUR-DAY.jpg)
[Image source](https://www.scotthyoung.com/blog/2007/08/28/the-critical-7-rules-to-understand-people/)

Understanding people is supremely critical for an entrepreneur. Whether it is understanding consumer, client, venture capitalist or who to hire in your team, understanding human psychology and behaviour takes on a long way. Understanding and evolving the business needs based on consumer needs, and understanding the financier's mindset and areas of concern will keep capital flowing and business growing.

Be Financially Savvy

![5cd4ed2e1f000058009c126a.jpeg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmP4Vm4zYCNMoWNnnSPpd4mg9jSS9g4uFMnHV1rZNBjGZR/5cd4ed2e1f000058009c126a.jpeg)
[Image source](https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2017/08/28/financial-quiz_a_23049194/)

This can't be emphasized enough. Knowing the burn rate of your business and when is it likely to become self sustaining will help plan your resources better. Think about how many dApp treasuries didn't plan their financing and were forced to fire people and slow down development in the bear market. Planning capex and marketing at the right time and allocating resources prudently helps make successful entrepreneurs grow business faster than others. 

That's what I think. If you liked the article and want to read more such articles or discuss entrepreneurship, please join Intrepreneur on [discord](https://discord.gg/U7VbkHm)

Posted using [Partiko Android](https://partiko.app/referral/karamyog)
root_title: Intrepreneur Quest - How to be a successful entrepreneur?

title: Ultraviolet and Infrared Photography - Play structure at Chattahoochee Bend State Park
body:
I was wrapping up my adventure for the day at this state park, when I came across a really cool looking play structure tucked away with no one around.

These photos are my posts for #colorchallenge

[![rw-1190445.jpeg](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190445.jpeg)](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190445.jpeg) https://s8.postimg.cc/5w0d1f991/panasonic_dmcgh3.png Camera Model|Lumix GH3, modified by LifePixel for Full Spectrum| -|-| https://s8.postimg.cc/foc7yf96d/lens.png Lens | Olympus M.ZUIKO DIGITAL ED 12mm-50mm https://s8.postimg.cc/p8vuli8ut/cropfilter1.png Filter| B+W UV Black (403) Filter https://s8.postimg.cc/r1u5wcrvp/apture.png Aperture| f/3.8 https://s8.postimg.cc/89iassimt/Timeexposurevalue.png Shutter Speed | 1/500 sec| https://s8.postimg.cc/kqoyfm5z9/iso.png Film Speed| 800| https://s8.postimg.cc/fpm5rwvlh/spectrum.png Spectrum| Ultraviolet-A and Infrared (UVA and IR) https://s8.postimg.cc/63slc3wv9/wavelengh1.png Wavelength| 320 to 385 nm and 750 nanometers https://s8.postimg.cc/wd92h2lo5/location.png Location| Chattahoochee Bend State Park GA, USA. [![rw-1190444.jpeg](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190444.jpeg)](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190444.jpeg) I took a little time and took some photos of this interesting looking structure, along with the ultraviolet blue sky casting through the support beams and ropes. [![rw-1190447.jpeg](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190447.jpeg)](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190447.jpeg) It was a sunny day and nice and bright out on the playground, made for good photography. [![rw-1190448.jpeg](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190448.jpeg)](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190448.jpeg) There was a rope swing as well, alot of fun features to play with. [![rw-1190451.jpeg](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190451.jpeg)](https://makingblocks.xyz/@solominer:b/rw-1190451.jpeg) I really enjoyed seeing all the rope work included in this structure. It was a great design for a state park. After putting my camera down I played on it a little myself. https://spee.ch/@solominer:c/speech-lbry.png These images are being hosted by Spee.ch An image hosting service on top of the LBRY protocol. ### [Makingblocks.xyz/about](Makingblocks.xyz/about) --- I take pictures with a special camera. Its a Mirrorless DSLR that has been modified by Life Pixel to see light in other wavelengths. This allows my camera to see light in the Infrared [IR] around 1300 NM wavelength, through the visual spectrum and into the Ultraviolet A and B wavelengths roughly into the 300 NM wavelength. I carry many filters on me to make the photos you see in my blog, these filters screw on my lens and help me isolate certain wavelengths for certain scenes. These filters can be IR / UV pass-through filters to assist me get a natural photo taking out the UV and IR light. Or I may use a Infrared pass-through filter capture just IR light. I can do the same with UV light as well, though I need some better filters which they can cost a few hundred dollars for true Ultraviolet pass through filters. So for right now I have B + W 403 bandpass filters that still allow some IR light in, due to their cheaper material.

There are also exotic glasses made of sapphire and germanium I am open to working with to replace my silica glass hot mirror with a material that allows even longer wavelengths of infrared to enter my cameras sensor. Special sensors, lenses and filters of that material would be needed as well, so it would be a big project but one that may give some even more unique photography results.

body:

<center>[Source](https://xrc.bomboradyo.com/newscenter/2019/07/Gilas-Pilipinas.jpg)</center>

Gilas Pilipinas coach Yeng Guaio has no time to prepare for the upcoming FIBA World Cup held in China at the end of the month.

Although only nine players attended their practice last night at the Meralco Gym, they continued.

Gabe Norwood has suffered a mild groin strain injury from playing for eight days in Spain but is expected to return in the coming days.

Guiao did not hide his admiration for two rookies CJ Perez and Robert Bolick who made a good showing in their training camp.

There are two more tune-up games to do this Gilas visit Australia's Adelaide 36ers National Basketball League (NBL) before their trip to China on August 29.

author: honeybee
title: A helpful overview of the Supreme Court's current standing in public opinion.
body:
[![](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmYEA9vnGZGLbLC1MzjmWfLp5qBGsfQPQbZhZkg1Wepjtr/image.png)](https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/can-the-supreme-court-stay-above-the-partisan-fray/)

For now, a few brief thoughts:

1. The Court has a whopping 62% approval rating - a level Trump or Congress would kill for. For the moment, the Kavanaugh confirmation has joined a long series of other events that partisans on one side or the other thought would seriously damage the Court's legitimacy, but ended up largely failing to do so (e.g.Roe v. Wade, Bush v. Gore, Citizens United, The Bork and Thomas confirmation battles, etc.).

2. However, the growing partisan divide over the Court is still notable. If Democrats continue to get more unhappy with the Court, the potential to mobilise them against it will grow.

3. Much of the Court's public support is relatively "soft." We don't really know what would happen if a popular Democratic president (or, for that matter, a GOP one) made a determined effort to rally his or her party to the cause of court-packing or some other effort to neuter the Court. Nothing like that has happened since 1937. While FDR failed then, it is by no means clear a similar effort would fail today, given various changes in political conditions.

4. I should emphasise I am NOT claiming that the Court's popularity somehow proves the justices are doing a good job. As I have noted many times before, most voters know very little about the court's work (as is also true of much of the activity of the other branches of government) and public opinion is -at best - a weak indicator of quality. Similarly, the Court's continued popularity does not prove that Kavanaugh deserved to be confirmed or that confirmation process was handled well.
root_title: A helpful overview of the Supreme Court's current standing in public opinion.

![JvFFVmatwWHRfvmtd53nmEJ94xpKydwmbSC5H5svBACH81bJTo1AEJHvmVcxNuEyASpuHogyCh5xitG1E6z9SQPohqtY4Fk6j1dPxeNUHQsJ7jXbbLD2WjPQA2PWw34ijhafQjBbTk.jpeg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmbsHLTbAeYYxb6XwWBSTo3H5amWgL4UJyj6M4NkhNiVL3/JvFFVmatwWHRfvmtd53nmEJ94xpKydwmbSC5H5svBACH81bJTo1AEJHvmVcxNuEyASpuHogyCh5xitG1E6z9SQPohqtY4Fk6j1dPxeNUHQsJ7jXbbLD2WjPQA2PWw34ijhafQjBbTk.jpeg)

It is no longer a rumor that the blockchain technology is taking over the transaction platform since the inception of Bitcoin in 2009 it has become a revolutionary method of payment which is intended to become the major means of transaction over the traditional method but this does not means that this technology does not have flaws and limitations, the blockchain technology currently faces acceptability problem as well as the inability of the entire audience of the world to fully trust it enough before adopting  it as a major means of transaction, Bitcoin has set out a platform for others by creating a digital peer to peer  transactions, bitcoin has also depicted how the future of the digital communities  and the system of networking looks like, although Bitcoin has demonstrated great level of sustainability, manageability in crypto currency which has made a large percentage in the global community accepted it as a means of payment, nevertheless, blockchain technology has over the years faced some major setbacks and restrictions in reaching out to innovators, corporations and other entrepreneurs in the globe, though the introduction of bitcoin and etherium has given the blockchain technology an edge in the areas such as ; creation of global collaborative communities, a decentralized system and open software for transaction platform but has failed to solve the unavoidable problems such as; scalability issues, programming problems, blockchain insecurity, usability problems and computational technology issues, these are the problems that TEMTUM has come to solve.

SCALABILTY ISSUES
The earlier generation of blockchain technology (Bitcoin and etherium) has really confined the users this is because there is a maximum number of transaction , limitation in block size by bitcoin, the amount of gas in the block restrictions for conventional blockchains in transactional output and the linear linked-list style blockchain which does not really accelerate  scalability. 

BLOCKCHAIN INSECURITY
Despite the fact that the first generational blockchain use protocol layer protection the application layer security is still not a very good one this has caused delay and unnecessary holding of Ether.

USABILITY 
There is need for third party centralized tools of specialized hardware to make up for more space and targeting of mobile platforms  for driving heavy deployments is also carried out using light client implementations.

![0.jpeg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmcRHzx6vdufZYNBm2SXU6P3zztjxvWdv6LANqg2r7GdEU/0.jpeg)

ABOUT TEMTUM
TEMTUM is a compository subject which is made up of two concepts called temporal blockchain (tem)and quantum randomness (temtum) which is a bockchain technology that transforms the way blockchain works, this it achieves by reconstruction of pere to peer networks scale, with temtum the goal of having a fully scalable network decentralized is possible, temtum cryptocurrency depicts a compelling large market at the international level. This it achieve by operating with an unparalleled degree of security guaranteed transaction carried out with a low resourced devices at extremely high speeds, TEMTUM has come to address the major problems faced by the current blockchain technology which include; scalabilty, speed, resource intensity and security, temtum uses technology such as achievable blockchain, consensus algorithm, routing algorithm and NIST randomness Beacon to achieve effective temporal blockchain network.

HOW TO SOLVE THE PROBLEMS BY TEMTUM

Scalability	
The TEMTUM achives data locally thereby eliminating the storage of the whole chain history on the nodes involved, this gives access to more users with a low resource device such as smartphones to fully participates in the network and thereby providing an infinite scalabilty and establishing a decentralized scales.

Speed
The speed of the temtum network is unlimited provided the hardware and the bandwidth is of the user is in support, malicious fork does not exist here unlike in bitcoin and block size limitations has been cancelled and a concensus algorithm which very efficient and effective has been created.

Security
The network is not vulnerable and it has the immunity to theoretical attacks by using photon source for genuine random number generation plus next generation hashing algorithms.

author: abh12345
title: Can I draw a picture, daddy?
body:
More of my daughters early artwork to share today, and this stuff predates the images on the [post](https://steemit.com/photography/@abh12345/through-her-lens) I submitted a week or so ago.

At some point I'll have to get the earliest works (in which real paper was used!) scanned but for now, 11 of the 14 images I have saved from around 7/8 years ago.

![rainbow world.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/FiEVr4jv-rainbow20world.png)

-------------------

The images were all made in Paint. I first used this application at school (probably a few years older than my daughter at the time she made these) and can remember how difficult it was to guide a cursor with this plastic thing the teachers called a Mouse.

![pretty flowers.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/vPnSNnE8-pretty20flowers.png)

I do remember detailing the basics - how to choose different colours, delete/remove things, and change between the brushes and fill option (90% of the app. then) but she was mostly left to her own devices and the ideas on what to draw certainly weren't mine.

![boats on the sea.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/xyjuTH97-boats20on20the20sea.png)

A year or so previously, I'd taken my daughter to Portugal for the week and we spent a lot of time at the beach from which you could see a small harbor.  The small shells on the photo above are pretty cool :)

![apple tree with daddy and katy and me.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/cAQHHNWY-apple20tree20with20daddy20and20katy20and20me.png)

It was my job to save the files once complete and I'd try to get a name for the work - The above was named 'Apple tree with daddy and Katy and Me'.

![rainbow and big flower.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/DD240LQJ-rainbow20and20big20flower.png)

![the starry morning with rainbows and bright sunshine.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/mjp4s89e-the20starry20morning20with20rainbows20and20bright20sunshine.png)

![sunshine and rainbow and rain and daffodil.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/wIDQLaMx-sunshine20and20rainbow20and20rain20and20daffodil.png)

Rainbows, flowers, and cats seemed to be prominent in the mind of a 4/5 year old girl.  That's the way it should be isn't it? :)

![happybithdaykaty.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/EgxR7LAb-happybithdaykaty.png)

More love for Katy the (toy/teddy) cat - a gift from her late great-grandma which was (and still might be) cherished by my daughter for years after she passed.  I actually found it comforting when I saw the cat each week as it reminded me of my lovely gran.

![fireworks with rainbows2.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/BhyjweDG-fireworks20with20rainbows2.png)

Fireworks and a rainbow, imagine that - she did :)

![dad.png](https://files.steempeak.com/file/steempeak/abh12345/GlDBRAIo-dad.png)

<3

author: majes.tytyty
title: “All Tomorrow’s Parties,” covered by Japan … (New Wave / Post-Punk – Music to Your Ears, Covers–38)
body:
https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmWvFpmGa7Qa2o7vc8kJY5cByWFRDcEJX5z6oApVxh2iKf/image.png

The superb musicianship and Sylvian’s crooning vocals hint that everything might not be so bad.
https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmdz2ZhBjZ2soqfYDYFSsCKz5i1tjHDUzBBbz7bwh19aA6/image.png

Japan – “All Tomorrow’s Parties”

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R7tZbI_ITus https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmdz2ZhBjZ2soqfYDYFSsCKz5i1tjHDUzBBbz7bwh19aA6/image.png

https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmezLeneD7wGjEdqCBFkpZiH7F81BhEwCFo5JcA3DuaEMk/image.png

“All Tomorrow’s Parties” (1979 – original from 1967)

With this cover of one of the most beautiful Velvet Underground songs, the UK post-punk band Japan managed the rare feat of equalling the excellent original version. And in some way, they may even have surpassed it. 

Gloom and Misery

In the original VU version of “All Tomorrow’s Parties,”  Nico’s glacial delivery made us believe that the protagonist had no hope, no alternatives, and that the poor girl was doomed to long nights and longer days of loneliness, gloom, and misery.

Comfort and Quiet

https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmNTQUrayUanyKsAJ3M4Tkfcdtcw9Ba1TpruZUfjXmPAkh/image.png
In Japan’s rendition, however, the superb musicianship and David Sylvian’s crooning vocals hint that everything might not be so bad, and that the girl might have better things to do than go to parties where she may not feel welcome or comfortable.   

This version ends with a long, slow fade-out. It’s as if the girl has turned away from the party, and is now strolling towards a more inviting destination – towards, maybe, a pleasant “quiet life.”   (Image source) https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmdz2ZhBjZ2soqfYDYFSsCKz5i1tjHDUzBBbz7bwh19aA6/image.png

Japan

Japan was a UK new wave band. At first glance, the band may have appeared to be a glam-rock or new romantic group. But even a brief listen to its music will show that Japan was more of a post-punk art-rock band.  

Any Place but Home … and the US

The band’s first 2 albums received minimal attention in its homeland the UK, and virtually none in the US. But in Canada, Japan, and the Netherlands, the band attracted cult followings. In fact, the single “Adolescent Sex”  became a Top-30 hit in the Netherlands.   

In 1979, with their 3rd album, Japan became relatively successful in the UK too, with 9 of its songs making it into the Top 40.  

Best Not Forgotten

https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmRsFsERcBNZFREP8Q1Z9c19uQcEXjjJ7WXviBzvKiDT8V/image.png
The band’s 5th and final album, 1981’s ground-breaking “Tin Drum,”  achieved Silver status within a month of its release, and reached Gold within 4 months.

author: glenalbrethsen
title: Grandpa Gotta Cook—Butter Chicken
body:
### If At First You Don't Succeed...
I imagine many of you are familiar with the saying, *If at first you don't succeed...*

No, it doesn't end with, *...go cry to your mother.* It states, *...try, try again.* Meaning, that just because the first attempt ended in failure, does not mean you are destined to fail every time. However, without doing more, you're not likely to know. You need to keep with it until success is achieved.

![IMG_2294.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmXQB1N97eFcw1CAJAbRGHUGNpnEXAWnrpX1CttNo7e8qs/IMG_2294.JPG)

With that in mind, I take you back six weeks when I made an Indian dish called Tikka Masala.

You will remember, it didn't turn out according to plan. Way too much cayenne pepper.

At the time, it didn't dawn on me that the part requiring cayenne pepper was homemade curry. Duh! I could have just bought that part if I'd known, and let the experts ensure the cayenne pepper was proportional to the overall taste.

Well, I didn't try Tikka Masala again, but I did cook up some Butter Chicken, which is similar to Tikka Masala, but not as much tomato product, and actual curry seasoning rather than making it myself.

The results? We'll get to those in a minute.

![IMG_2296.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmbnEzkFrSXP8pap5xQ6oFT8tsaqVWqfFsraTFMKH5S9Q2/IMG_2296.JPG)

This particular recipe for Butter Chicken was geared to the crockpot. Yep, I dusted off the old slow cooker again. It also called for chicken stock, tomato paste, yellow curry powder, garam masala, ground turmeric, salt, black pepper, chunks of chicken, onions, garlic, ginger, heavy cream, lime juice and brown sugar.

![IMG_2299.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmT3wiYEhXyRG4JxgvpXYcjWoRJ2131sYuoVyF3NQoavqJ/IMG_2299.JPG)

You'll notice that butter isn't a part of a recipe for Butter Chicken. Go figure. Perhaps the heavy cream is the butter? There were other recipes that called for butter along with heavy cream, so just to make it live up to its name, I put in a couple of tablespoons of butter.

In following the directions, I got a little ahead of myself. Everything but the heavy cream, lime juice and brown sugar are supposed to be mixed into a bowl and then poured over the chicken chunks. I ended up throwing the heavy cream in, too, and then wondering what that might do to it for the next three and a half hours.

![IMG_2295.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmNQwnAg2NRycEPpvHmze7KLZUMqMw6vPYEJqdRywjfHPd/IMG_2295.JPG)

The recipe called for four hours on low. It also said twenty minutes of prep. It took me at least forty minutes, plus I started late, so I let the crockpot cook on low for about two hours, then I cranked it up to high for another hour-ish. The chicken needed the extra cooking oomph, since at two hours the chunks were still only partially cooked.

![IMG_2297.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmRui8DuXqVLETTtzaWQEoTFyFchEkDAvVLzk2QtKL3vBE/IMG_2297.JPG)

With about twenty or so minutes to go, I started the rice, and then with about five minutes remaining, I put the Naan bread in to warm up. I put in the rest of the ingredients and waited. The rice took a little longer, but about five minutes later, everything was ready to go.

![IMG_2298.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmPh9XcVdofFJTeytTcCBDc7VCMyWijpMsPseBwgPv2ikE/IMG_2298.JPG)

#### And The Winner Is...

Me! Yes, I'm claiming victory on this one, people. I toned down the curry just a tad, and played up a little bit of the other ingredients that I knew people would like, and voila, it was a hit! My wife immediately said it was very good the moment she tasted it. The youngest son went back for more, and I thoroughly enjoyed it. I did not hear what the daughter-in-law thought as she was feeding the baby while the rest of us ate. I'll just say she liked it, too.

![IMG_2300.JPG](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmZwUiWpJ8QYpGghd6xR3JhTc7YbP4u2txBSoB2F5wtaLE/IMG_2300.JPG)

Objectives in using this recipe were met. Not so much tomato tasting ingredients (6 ounces of paste as opposed to 29 ounces of tomato sauce last time), not so spicy hot that it detracted from the rest of the flavors, and something with butter in it. I don't know if the butter actually came through or not. More butter maybe?

Oh, and having the cream in there cooking for three hours instead of poured in at the end didn't seem to detract from anything. Next time I do it, I will make it the right way to make sure.

#### You Know It's Good...
I couldn't wait to have more the next day for lunch. Having more Naan bread had little to do with it. I did forego the rice, though. One set of carbs the second time around was more than enough.

I'm glad I decided to try this other dish and find some Indian food my family really likes. Gives us another ethnic food to try on occasion. We could stand a little variety here and there, right?

So, until next time...

...Enjoy!

<sub>*Images courtesy of Glen Anthony Albrethsen*</sub>

*This post was published in conjunction with the weekly contest known far and wide as Food Fight Friday. Anyone is welcome to participate. To do so, simply write a post about food, post it on Friday, your time, use the #fff tag so others can find it, and then go and look at other posts. You'll have a chance to pick your favorite from among the entries. That's it. Winners receive shares of SBI.*

author: rezoanulvibes
title: How To Avoid Aggressive Attack For Self Defense
body:
When you fight in a match, you know it very well what you can do and what you cannot do. And you are very sure that what your opponent can or cannot do. There are rules in a fighting competition. Judges are sitting there. If anyone does not follow the rules, he or she will be disqualified. So you are bound to follow the rules and fight in a certain way.

![Aggressive attack.jpg](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmNN5GZAwNVoAxNWETQYzsf479HKREZyhyzFNMECbNErLS/Aggressive%20attack.jpg)
<sub>[Source](https://unsplash.com/photos/qbf59TU077Q)</sub>

If you are in an MMA fight, there are specific rules for that. If you are in the boxing competition, you will also see specific rules of striking. There are certain parts of the body where you cannot hit. You wear safety guards, mouthguards gloves, and so on. All of these are done for your safety and protection. 

When you fight in a competition, that's sports. When you fight on the street, that's for life, meaning, you focus on self defense and getting out of there alive.

Your opponent can attack you aggressively in a fighting match. The thing to remember is that no matter how aggressive your opponent is, there are always rules in a fighting competition.

## How about if someone is aggressive to attack, and there are no rules?

That's what we face in real life. You can get an attack at any time anywhere. Maybe you are in a shopping mall or walking on the street or in a restaurant. You don't know what is going to happen next. There is no referee to stop that. You are on your own.

https://youtu.be/Mwg18V2xS8c

Someone attacks you with punch or kick, you do not know whether he has any weapon or not. If he pulls out his gun and point at you, the situation will be changed. Or, he has a knife and now he is going to attack with the knife. Or, you do not know what he is capable of doing. He might have some background that puts him in a better position in the fighting.

So never underestimate your opponent. Before the attack, attackers can talk to you in a rough way. If you can stop him right there, and walk away, that's better. You know how to fight does not mean you have to fight. And every situation does not necessarily end up with fighting. You can stop a lot of things before getting into a fight. 

If the attacker attacks you, defend that and take control of the situation, see if he has some weapons or not. Your every movement should be in a certain order that works for you.  And make sure that the attacker cannot attack you back or if he does, just put him in a more vulnerable position. 

You can call the police. They take care of the situation. And you should leave the danger zone as soon as possible. 

Thank you so much for taking the time to read this post. If you find it useful, please follow me @RezoanulVibes to read more posts in the future. Please feel free to let me know your thoughts in the comment section. 

Stay safe. Always be happy!

[How Can Martial Arts Help You Dealing With Bullies](https://www.sportstalksocial.com/combat/@rezoanulvibes/how-can-martial-arts-help-you-dealing-with-bullies)

title: [Weather] 전국 자외선, 미세먼지, 초미세먼지 현황 정보
body:
전국 자외선, 미세먼지, 초미세먼지 현황 정보입니다.

---
[1] 아래 그림은 자외선 현황 정보 입니다.
![](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmNhppM9TGaWKLnwuB1H7yBm7WUgX4hXpLeKTMass1JBDh/image.png)

현재 자외선은 전국 보통수준입니다.

---
[2] 아래 그림은 미세먼지(입자 지름 2.5μm초과~10μm미만) 현황 정보입니다.
![](https://cdn.steemitimages.com/DQmSYeWDz9bg7pUk88uW8UWHKk4qH2sJuW5QPBchYuCxAEK/image.png)

title: Beautiful Candy Apples, Getting Creative with a classic Treat.
body:
I think this coming week I am going to embark on a creative journey and try and make my own candy apples like these ones in the photo but maybe with some alternate colors.  I found all kinds of cool recipes online so you can make them any color and add glitter even to make them truly beautiful.  Look at the purple one, the way it shines is just amazing and I'm sure it tastes just as good as any classic red candy apple.  I think my favorite part is the base, how the candy and sugar spreads outwards and creates an awesome little stand.  There is something about the texture that is very satisfying to look at, it looks soft and gooey but it's rock hard and can be snapped apart to have little bitesize pieces.
